Built application locally (JAR)
Built Docker Images (image)
Pushed to Nexus Repository (Nexus)

Developer --> Git Repo --> Should be tested and build

AVOIDING:
- stash working changes and move to Master Branch - update local state
- login to correct Docker Repository
- set up the test enironment to run tests
- execute tests (meanwhile you CAN'T code
- build Docker Image and push to repo

Test Code --> Build application --> Push to Repository --> Deploy to server = BUILD AUTOMATION
- Run tests
- Build artifacts
- Publish artifacts
- Deploy artifacts
- Send notifications
- and more!

JENKINS:
Docker
Build Tools
Repositories
Deployment Servers

- install Jenkins and prepare everything
- setup needs to be done only once
- plugins, credentials etc. can be used for different projects
